      "kind": "working_space_divergence",
      "summary": "PAEColorize luma-remap: matches FCP EXACTLY when Remap Black=[0,0,0] (black0_white_red, black0_white1 \u2014 both <0.5 level), but DIVERGES when the black point is NONZERO (black_blue_white_yellow: gray(64)->FCP[64,64,67] vs TS[64,64,191], up to 124 levels). The B channel (black_B=1,white_B=0 => remap=1-luma) decays FAR faster in FCP than the sRGB 1-luma mix, and neither sRGB nor linear luma/mix reproduces it.",
      "diagnosis": "Same working-space root cause as Brightness/Tint: the black->white luma mix is computed in a NON-sRGB working space (linear or an HGColorGamma stage), so it only agrees with the TS sRGB mix at the degenerate black=0 endpoint (where mix=luma*white is space-invariant at 0). A nonzero black point exposes the space mismatch. The TS colorizeRemapFilter does the mix in sRGB.",
      "oracle_truth_caveat": "oracle_truth=gui: colour family, headless!=GUI. The linear-working-space form that matches this headless transfer may regress the GUI gate (same class as Colorize's faithful/state.json DIVERGED note: 's2l endpoints matched headless but -11 NET on the GUI gate'). So this is CHARACTERIZED (working-space, gate-blocked), consistent with the faithful program's Colorize finding.",
